1417
01:25:16.010 --> 01:25:17.910
Are you kidding me?

1418
01:25:17.930 --> 01:25:20.020
You think I live at the ritz?

1419
01:25:23.710 --> 01:25:26.530
Have a cup of coffee with me?

1420
01:25:28.070 --> 01:25:29.900
What?

1421
01:25:37.120 --> 01:25:39.490
Do me a favor.

1422
01:25:41.240 --> 01:25:43.210
Save my life.

1423
01:25:51.630 --> 01:25:52.610
Get him! Get him!

1424
01:25:52.630 --> 01:25:53.950
Off the ropes! Off the ropes!

1425
01:25:53.970 --> 01:25:55.570
Oh, he missed him.

1426
01:25:55.590 --> 01:25:58.020
Oh, oh, oh, yeah, he did!

1427
01:25:58.040 --> 01:25:59.420
Bam-ba-bam-ba-bam-ba-bam!

1428
01:25:59.440 --> 01:26:02.210
Oh, oh, come on, bleed, dude.

1429
01:26:02.230 --> 01:26:03.420
Announcer: Distraction
from the imperial...

1430
01:26:03.440 --> 01:26:04.580
Oh, he's got him. Give the ddt!

1431
01:26:04.600 --> 01:26:06.220
What?

1432
01:26:06.240 --> 01:26:07.340
It's gonna be a ddt.

1433
01:26:07.360 --> 01:26:08.800
Up he goes,
and drop him on his head!

1434
01:26:10.180 --> 01:26:13.000
Oh, he's dead. He's dead.

1435
01:26:13.020 --> 01:26:14.550
Ok, fearless,
get out of the ring.

1436
01:26:14.570 --> 01:26:15.610
What do you mean,
get out of the ring?

1437
01:26:15.630 --> 01:26:16.640
You can't get out of t ring.

1438
01:26:16.660 --> 01:26:17.890
Yes, he can.
He has to get a chair.

1439
01:26:17.910 --> 01:26:19.230
A chair?

1440
01:26:20.920 --> 01:26:21.980
Bam!

1441
01:26:22.000 --> 01:26:23.690
Aah!

1442
01:26:23.710 --> 01:26:24.710
Slow motion.

1443
01:26:28.130 --> 01:26:29.500
Hyah!

1444
01:26:29.520 --> 01:26:32.190
Trevor, when did you
become so violent?

1445
01:26:32.210 --> 01:26:34.590
Oh, no, no, no.
Take me to a match.

1446
01:26:34.610 --> 01:26:36.060
You get splattered
in the front row.

1447
01:26:36.080 --> 01:26:37.430
I don't want to be
splattered, thank you...

1448
01:26:37.450 --> 01:26:39.570
Yes, you do. It'll be, like,

1449
01:26:39.590 --> 01:26:40.940
Your birthday present to me.

1450
01:26:40.960 --> 01:26:42.160
Oh, no. You know what you're
getting for your birthday?

1451
01:26:42.180 --> 01:26:43.160
What?

1452
01:26:43.180 --> 01:26:44.530
A brand-new encyclopedia...

1453
01:26:44.550 --> 01:26:45.750
Oh, ohh.

1454
01:26:45.770 --> 01:26:47.100
Leather-bound...

1455
01:26:47.120 --> 01:26:50.190
Thucydides' history
of the peloponnesian war.

1456
01:26:50.210 --> 01:26:52.780
No, I'm getting you
51 crackling volumes.

1457
01:26:52.800 --> 01:26:55.750
There'll be
pop quizzes every day.

1458
01:26:55.770 --> 01:26:57.790
On the development
of cotton farms...

1459
01:26:57.810 --> 01:26:58.790
Hi, arlene.

1460
01:26:58.810 --> 01:27:00.280
Unh!

1461
01:27:45.310 --> 01:27:47.730
You can't stay here, ricky.

1462
01:27:47.750 --> 01:27:49.700
I know.

1463
01:27:49.720 --> 01:27:51.370
Look, I know what we had.

1464
01:27:51.390 --> 01:27:53.160
Was a nightmare, arlene,

1465
01:27:53.180 --> 01:27:55.410
But I did it.

1466
01:27:55.430 --> 01:27:56.750
You did what?

1467
01:27:56.770 --> 01:27:58.470
I knew I couldn't come back.

1468
01:27:58.490 --> 01:28:01.360
To this house
unless I was sober.

1469
01:28:02.780 --> 01:28:05.100
It's the truth.

1470
01:28:05.120 --> 01:28:08.360
5 months, 2 weeks, and 4 days.

1471
01:28:08.380 --> 01:28:09.860
Of the truth.

1472
01:28:11.210 --> 01:28:12.360
Where you been?

1473
01:28:12.380 --> 01:28:13.830
What does it matter?

1474
01:28:13.850 --> 01:28:15.840
I knew I had to change.

1475
01:28:15.860 --> 01:28:17.870
Are you sober?

1476
01:28:17.890 --> 01:28:21.300
Yeah, and I got sober
staying right here.

1477
01:28:21.320 --> 01:28:23.130
Well, you're stronger than me.

1478
01:28:23.150 --> 01:28:25.360
Can you just stop
for a minute...

1479
01:28:25.380 --> 01:28:27.230
Please?

1480
01:28:27.250 --> 01:28:29.910
Can we just sit down and talk?

1481
01:28:31.920 --> 01:28:32.920
Ok.

1482
01:29:48.440 --> 01:29:49.420
Hi.

1483
01:29:49.440 --> 01:29:50.420
God!

1484
01:29:50.440 --> 01:29:52.260
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1485
01:29:52.280 --> 01:29:53.680
What are you doing here?

1486
01:29:53.700 --> 01:29:55.010
I want you to understand...

1487
01:29:55.030 --> 01:29:56.350
Oh, it's not necessary, really.

1488
01:29:56.370 --> 01:29:57.570
No explanation required.

1489
01:29:57.590 --> 01:30:00.020
Please don't talk
to me like that.

1490
01:30:00.040 --> 01:30:03.030
We had 13 years in, eugene.

1491
01:30:03.050 --> 01:30:04.190
He's sober now.

1492
01:30:04.210 --> 01:30:05.580
We've never been sober together.

1493
01:30:05.600 --> 01:30:06.700
Well, I wish you luck.

1494
01:30:06.720 --> 01:30:09.870
I feel like I gotta
give him a chance.

1495
01:30:09.890 --> 01:30:11.380
A chance?

1496
01:30:11.400 --> 01:30:12.510
A chance for what?

1497
01:30:12.530 --> 01:30:14.850
To change,

1498
01:30:14.870 --> 01:30:17.300
To try to make up for lost time.

1499
01:30:17.320 --> 01:30:19.640
Oh, what, to take trevor
to some ball games?

1500
01:30:19.660 --> 01:30:21.190
Do some real daddy
things with him?

1501
01:30:21.210 --> 01:30:22.200
Yeah.

1502
01:30:22.220 --> 01:30:23.900
He promised to try.

1503
01:30:23.920 --> 01:30:24.920
What do you want me to do?

1504
01:30:24.920 --> 01:30:26.300
Oh, I don't know, be smart.

1505
01:30:26.320 --> 01:30:27.440
He's his father, eugene.

1506
01:30:27.460 --> 01:30:29.190
He impregnated you, arlene.

1507
01:30:29.210 --> 01:30:31.780
In what other way has he
been a father to trevor?

1508
01:30:31.800 --> 01:30:34.900
Unless knocking somebody
around is a new family value.

1509
01:30:34.920 --> 01:30:36.240
What are you talking about?

1510
01:30:36.260 --> 01:30:37.580
He never touched trevor.

1511
01:30:37.600 --> 01:30:39.500
Oh, that's right.

1512
01:30:39.520 --> 01:30:41.250
Only you.

1513
01:30:41.270 --> 01:30:43.020
He only took it out on you.

1514
01:30:43.040 --> 01:30:44.660
That's so much better.

1515
01:30:47.920 --> 01:30:49.680
What did trevor tell you?

1516
01:30:49.700 --> 01:30:51.490
Enough.

1517
01:30:51.510 --> 01:30:54.110
Christ, arlene. Secrets
like that shouldn't be kept.

1518
01:30:54.130 --> 01:30:55.660
What good does it do trevor?

1519
01:30:55.680 --> 01:30:57.830
You weren't there.
Ricky never meant to hit me.

1520
01:30:57.850 --> 01:30:58.950
We were drunk...

1521
01:30:58.970 --> 01:31:01.440
Christ! What is it
with women like you?

1522
01:31:01.460 --> 01:31:02.770
Is that something you
really tell yourself?

1523
01:31:02.790 --> 01:31:05.500
"Oh, it's ok he beat me.
Trevor's ok"?

1524
01:31:05.520 --> 01:31:07.830
Trevor has locked
himself in a bathroom,

1525
01:31:07.850 --> 01:31:09.290
And he can't breathe,

1526
01:31:09.310 --> 01:31:11.090
And he's... and he's
hoping and praying.

1527
01:31:11.110 --> 01:31:12.090
That it will stop.

1528
01:31:12.110 --> 01:31:13.260
Trevor never went through...

1529
01:31:13.280 --> 01:31:15.300
How do you know what
trevor went through?

1530
01:31:15.320 --> 01:31:17.140
How do you know?

1531
01:31:17.160 --> 01:31:19.220
How do you know that
next time after you,

1532
01:31:19.240 --> 01:31:21.140
He doesn't come for trevor?

1533
01:31:21.160 --> 01:31:23.650
I know what I'm
talking about, arlene.

1534
01:31:23.670 --> 01:31:26.320
My father got on his knees.

1535
01:31:26.340 --> 01:31:27.790
And begged my mother,

1536
01:31:27.810 --> 01:31:28.910
And my mother,

1537
01:31:28.930 --> 01:31:30.830
She always took him back.

1538
01:31:30.850 --> 01:31:32.630
I never understood it.

1539
01:31:32.650 --> 01:31:34.340
She covered the bruises
and the cuts,

1540
01:31:34.360 --> 01:31:36.340
And she'd take him back.

1541
01:31:36.360 --> 01:31:38.490
Because he begged.

1542
01:31:38.510 --> 01:31:40.380
And he cried.

1543
01:31:40.400 --> 01:31:42.080
And now you ask me
what happened.

1544
01:31:42.100 --> 01:31:43.090
After he came back.

1545
01:31:43.110 --> 01:31:44.070
No... no, go on!

1546
01:31:44.090 --> 01:31:45.210
You said you wanted to know.

1547
01:31:45.230 --> 01:31:46.190
What happened to me.
Now ask me.

1548
01:31:46.210 --> 01:31:47.390
I don't like this.

1549
01:31:47.410 --> 01:31:49.550
Did he hurt you,
eugene? Ask me!

1550
01:31:51.050 --> 01:31:52.170
Did he hurt you?

1551
01:31:53.220 --> 01:31:54.790
Not for long.

1552
01:31:54.810 --> 01:31:58.000
By 13, I was gone.
I ran away...

1553
01:31:58.020 --> 01:31:59.920
But I missed her,

1554
01:31:59.940 --> 01:32:02.170
So I had to go back and see her.

1555
01:32:02.190 --> 01:32:05.090
And so one night, I did.

1556
01:32:05.110 --> 01:32:06.730
Now ask me what
happened that night.

1557
01:32:06.750 --> 01:32:08.940
What happened that night
you came back, eugene?

1558
01:32:08.960 --> 01:32:10.350
What happened?

1559
01:32:10.370 --> 01:32:11.770
He was there...

1560
01:32:11.790 --> 01:32:13.660
Drunk as usual.

1561
01:32:13.680 --> 01:32:15.750
Only this time,
I wasn't the same.

1562
01:32:15.770 --> 01:32:17.540
I was 16 years old,

1563
01:32:17.560 --> 01:32:20.040
And I was no longer
afraid of him.

1564
01:32:20.060 --> 01:32:21.710
And when I looked
him in the eye.

1565
01:32:21.730 --> 01:32:23.850
And told him if he
ever touched her again

1566
01:32:23.870 --> 01:32:24.850
I would kill him,

1567
01:32:24.870 --> 01:32:26.770
He knew...

1568
01:32:26.790 --> 01:32:28.720
He knew that
he would never exist.

1569
01:32:28.740 --> 01:32:30.980
For me again.

1570
01:32:31.000 --> 01:32:33.260
And I'm standing
in front of the house.

1571
01:32:33.280 --> 01:32:34.850
I'm telling her,

1572
01:32:34.870 --> 01:32:36.100
I'm screaming
for her to come out.

1573
01:32:36.120 --> 01:32:37.640
I'm telling her
she doesn't have to...

1574
01:32:37.660 --> 01:32:39.060
She doesn't have
to take it anymore.

1575
01:32:39.060 --> 01:32:40.040
She really doesn't.

1576
01:32:40.060 --> 01:32:41.060
She can come with me now.

1577
01:32:41.070 --> 01:32:42.430
I don't even see it coming.

1578
01:32:42.450 --> 01:32:43.550
He hits me in
the side of the head.

1579
01:32:43.570 --> 01:32:44.550
With a 2x4,

1580
01:32:44.570 --> 01:32:45.810
And I'm bleeding from my ear.

1581
01:32:45.830 --> 01:32:47.440
And then he's dragging me.

1582
01:32:47.460 --> 01:32:48.610
He's dragging me
behind the house.

1583
01:32:48.630 --> 01:32:49.980
And into the garage,
and then he's gone.

1584
01:32:50.000 --> 01:32:52.200
A minute, 5 minutes,
I don't know.

1585
01:32:52.220 --> 01:32:53.990
And then he's back, and
he's wetting me down.

1586
01:32:54.010 --> 01:32:56.460
He's wetting me down,
and I don't understand.

1587
01:32:56.480 --> 01:32:59.080
I don't understand why water...

1588
01:32:59.100 --> 01:33:01.920
Should smell so bad.

1589
01:33:01.940 --> 01:33:03.720
I don't understand.

1590
01:33:03.740 --> 01:33:06.650
And then I see it.

1591
01:33:06.670 --> 01:33:08.450
I see...

1592
01:33:10.920 --> 01:33:11.920
This...

1593
01:33:15.430 --> 01:33:17.250
This gas can,

1594
01:33:17.270 --> 01:33:22.560
This red gas can from his trunk.

1595
01:33:27.490 --> 01:33:30.490
And he looks at me
one last time...

1596
01:33:32.500 --> 01:33:34.250
And he lights a match.

1597
01:33:38.140 --> 01:33:41.050
And the last thing I remember...

1598
01:33:41.070 --> 01:33:43.580
And I'll never forget it...

1599
01:33:43.600 --> 01:33:45.400
Were his eyes.

1600
01:33:47.190 --> 01:33:51.180
His eyes because they
were filled with this...

1601
01:33:51.200 --> 01:33:54.690
Immense...

1602
01:33:54.710 --> 01:33:57.880
Satisfaction.

1603
01:34:00.720 --> 01:34:02.120
I'm so sorry...

1604
01:34:02.140 --> 01:34:05.940
Don't... don't... don't tell me
how sorry you are for me!

1605
01:34:05.960 --> 01:34:07.980
Just tell me how
you're gonna stop it.

1606
01:34:08.000 --> 01:34:09.020
Happening to trevor.

1607
01:34:09.040 --> 01:34:11.490
Ricky would never do that.

1608
01:34:11.510 --> 01:34:15.010
Oh, jesus, arlene.
He doesn't have to.

1609
01:34:17.100 --> 01:34:19.270
All he has to do
is not love him.

1610
01:35:19.540 --> 01:35:20.540
